- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves combinatorial arguments and lower bounds.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of reducing graphs on surfaces, which has applications in game theory and social choice theory.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with graph transformations, which is a topic relevant to network analysis.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves lower bounds on the number of transformations required to reduce a graph, which is a topic in algorithmic complexity.
